This is the sea view from the flat’s patio.  The flat is located on the seafront of Aliki’s coast with little - practically none - distance from the beach.
Here is some of the patio furniture we provide. Our guests can relax by reading a book or editing photos for their instagram account whilst enjoying a cup of tea.
The bedroom includes a double-sized bed, a single bed, a large closet and an AC for those who wish to adjust the room’s temperature.
This is the closet in the bedroom.
The bathroom includes a high-pressure shower, a washing machine (an initial amount of washer-friendly soap is provided by us) and a window to keep the air refreshed.
The bathroom includes a washing machine.
In the kitchen you’ll find a toastier maker, a kettle, an espresso machine with some capsules and all of the cutlery & cookery essentials.
This is a wide space with a dining table, 2 single beds, that can also be used as sofas, an AC, a smart TV and with the kitchen being located on the right side of the photo.

This is the pathway in front of the flat’s patio. Right around the corner of the left you have the main beach of Aliki and on the right side you have a public parking space - for those who have a vehicle at their disposal.
This is how the flat looks from the outside when you arrive. There’s car access up to the entrance point of the flat - in case there’s a case of disability amongst our guests.
This is the flat’s patio. It is slightly elevated from the path in the front.

This is the Western part of the Aliki village. Aliki has been a fishing village through its existence and the old houses were built along the coast line. Barewake’s Place used to be a big family household that could house both family and friends.
This is a drone overview of the wider Aliki region. The drone being positioned South-West to the settlement.
Right in front of Barewake’s Place, there’s a small port that’s a nice spot to enjoy some calm time reading a book, observing the seagulls and wondering how do those crabs fit under those rocks!
This is how the Aliki bay looks from the Barewake’s place side - the west side of Aliki beach.
Peace & Quiet. This is how the beach looks on a cloudy autumnal day. The photo was taken during fall which is technically off-season but the place is uniquely magical at that time.

This boat is the one we take wake boarding and wake surfing. Typically, we’d spend a whole day in the sea with our friends - chilling in distant corners of wee islands and then we’d return to Barewake’s Place to prepare dinner and unwind in the patio
This is the 3rd closest beach - in walking distance. It’s called Pisso Aliki and it's right behind the shops and taverns of Aliki port.
This is where the path starts to gets you to Markia Myti. It starts from Agios Nikolaos beach and it takes you around the coastline to find one-of-a-kind seascapes.
This is Agios Nikolaos beach. It’s a 5’ walking distance away from the flat. Crystal clear blue waters and plenty of hideouts for snorkeling.
One of the hidden gems found in the natural stone works of the Southern Paros. The place awaits explorers and nature lovers to discover its hidden beauty.

The bedroom is a 10'x12' freestanding canvas tent with proper spring coil mattress atop a 4 poster bed with luxe 100% linen sheets, feather pillows in two sizes, standard and Euro shams, a heated mattress pad so  you'll sleep warm as toast.
Dig this Vitruvian Man duvet, loaded with sacred geometry and esoteric symbols.

Ask about our romance options like Dead Sea Salt bath bombs, or a therapeutic massage, by appointment to take your getaway to the next level. There's also a yoga platform in the Zen Garden downstairs. Let us know if you want to do a load of laundry.
If you love a lightshow, we can set you up with a mini-LED color ball to make your stay memorable, and Instagrammable!
We provide wine glasses, an ice bucket (upon request) and cocktail shaker for a special evening libation you've been craving with your loved one.

Kitchen has most everything you need, cooking oil, dish soap, sponge, anti bacterial wipes and spray for Covid confidence, teas, coffee, sugar, creamer, filtered water available to refill from a 5 gallon bottle in laundry room.
The fridge has enough space for a weekend.
Kitchen has a microwave under the sink, and a fridge.
The wall mounted tv can be swiveled to view form tub or while sitting at kitchen table. We add some dvds we think you'll love to our Roku channels.

The tent comes with a private bathhouse oasis with romantic heartshaped jacuzzi built for two, a kitchen with two burner stove, fridge, microwave, bar sink, electic water heater for super fast coffee/tea time, cookware, barware, dishes, cutlery.

The bathroom sink and toilet are behind a custom antique mirrored barndoor. You'll find a vintage medicine cabinet where all your toiletries will fit, and a over-toilet cupboard. We supply the bath and hand towels, wash clothes, soap. shampoo, & robe
We lend you a record player in case you want to do some vinyl shopping. We can lend you a couple LPs to audition if you'd like, we also sell vintage vinyl.

The bed has loads of bedding for any weather scenario. There's 100% linen sheets, a woven cotton blanket, a faux fur throw, and a trippy Viruvian Man print duvet. If its chilly, top with our toasty vintage Irish knit blanket.
The bathhouse has a table and two chairs for meals, or dine al fresco on the rooftop deck. Or choose the table to do a little laptop work between enjoying the jacuzzi and rooftop deck.

The bed chamber has a romantic 4 poster bed, 2 nightstands with shelves for your stuff, matching Moroccan hanging lanterns, sheer lengths of silky fabric strewn from the  ceiling, and exotic tapestries hanging from the walls.
You'll sleep on a cloud with 4 feather pillows, two foam pillows and neck roll.

Above the fully equipped kitchen there's a television with Roku premium channels, a dvd player with a curated collection of Oscar contenders, a cd player/radio tuned to local college radio, and a selection of music cds to choose from.
